# Makefile Commands

## Source of truth

Project commands live in the **root [Makefile](Makefile)**. Prefer `make <target>` over ad-hoc `pixi run …` / raw `mojo …` in docs, agent workflows, and pre-commit checks.

Default test gate (see **no-commit-without-green-test**):

```bash
make test
```

## When to use make

| Situation | Command |
|-----------|---------|
| After Mojo edits | `make check` or `make build` |
| Before commit | `make test` |
| Grad regression | `make test-grad` |
| Quick train sanity | `make smoke` / `make smoke-cuda` |
| Real chain train | `make train` / `make train-cuda` |
| Teacher dataset | `make extract` |
| First-time setup | `make install` then `make setup` |

Use env-specific variants (`train-cpu`, `train-cuda`, `smoke-cpu`, `smoke-cuda`) instead of inline `CALIBER158_DEVICE=… pixi run …`.

## Keep Makefile in sync

When adding or renaming a user-facing command:

1. Add or update a **`.PHONY` target** in [Makefile](Makefile) with a `##` help line.
2. If the command is also a pixi task, update [pixi.toml](pixi.toml) and delegate from Make (`$(PIXI) <task>`).
3. If the command is the test gate or a required check, wire it into `make test` or document why it stays optional.
4. Update [README.md](README.md) / [HANDOFF.md](HANDOFF.md) quick-start snippets to `make …` where appropriate.

Do **not** duplicate long shell one-liners in rules or README when a Make target exists.

## Implementation notes

- `make build` runs `mojo build main.mojo` and **fails on any compiler warning** (zero-warning policy).
- GPU targets (`smoke-cuda`, `train-cuda`) require a compatible NVIDIA GPU visible at **compile and run** time.
- `make clean` is safe local cleanup only; it does not remove `data/` or `models/`.
